name: Rama
description:
Illustrations of Rama
Rama was the eldest son of King Dasarata and Mother Kosalya. Where she got the nickname as Maryada Purushottama which means 'Perfect Man'. When he was a teenager, he won a competition and received a prize in the form of a wife named Dewi Shinta who was the incarnation of Dewi Laksmi. Until he was blessed with twins named Kusa and Lawa.
